    {
      "text": "Talking with someone is saying things to him, hearing what he says and taking in his meaning. People can talk together only when they have a language in common. When you were very young your parents talked to you and after a time you saw what they meant and learned to talk to them. A baby’s first words are commonly names for its parents. Some children learn to talk earlier than others.",
